blockStates.name: Bubble Plot
blockStates.userText:
A bubble plot is a type of plot that 
displays three dimensions of data. 
Each entity with its triplet (x, y, z) of 
associated data is plotted as a symbol,
typically a circle, that expresses two of
the values through the symbol's x and 
y coordinates and the third through 
its size.
